snippet: Earnings per share were above Wall Street expectations, but revenue was lower.
abstract: Humana reports drop in income due to higher claims payments from flu outbreak; reports fourth-quarter profit of $192 million, or $1.19 a share, down 3.5 percent from $199 million, or $1.20 a share, in year-ago quarter; revenue rose to $9.56 billion from $9.06 billion.
lead_paragraph: Earnings per share were above Wall Street expectations, but revenue was lower.

headline.seo: Humana’s Profits Reduced by a Bad Flu Season
headline.main: A Bad Flu Season Lowers Humana’s Profits
headline.print_headline: A Bad Flu Season Lowers Humana’s Profits
